your total cholesterol

00:39:00.470 --> 00:39:03.600
or your LDL, whichever
is the better of the two,

00:39:03.600 --> 00:39:06.590
and then your body mass index
or, if you're a bodybuilder,

00:39:06.590 --> 00:39:09.560
you can also use the
waist-to-height ratio.

00:39:09.560 --> 00:39:12.080
And then you see
how people score,

00:39:12.080 --> 00:39:16.460
and then that determines
what your discount is.

00:39:16.460 --> 00:39:19.540
So we had 11,000 team members,
almost 12,000 participate

00:39:19.540 --> 00:39:25.780
in '16, about 8,000 qualify
for higher-level discount card.

00:39:25.780 --> 00:39:28.220
And that saves our company.
it's a win-win-win strategy,

00:39:28.220 --> 00:39:30.170
because not only
are team members

00:39:30.170 --> 00:39:32.720
healthier as a result
of this incentive,

00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:34.830
but they save us a lot.

00:39:34.830 --> 00:39:35.657
We're self-insured.

00:39:35.657 --> 00:39:37.490
And probably Google is
self-insured as well.

00:39:42.381 --> 00:39:44.670
The company doesn't pay
anything for my health care.

00:39:44.670 --> 00:39:45.960
I never get sick.

00:39:45.960 --> 00:39:51.207
So if all of our team members
ate as healthy as I did,

00:39:51.207 --> 00:39:53.040
our health care-- we
spend over $200 million

00:39:53.040 --> 00:39:55.289
a year in health care for
our team members-- arguably,

00:39:55.289 --> 00:39:58.410
if everybody are
really healthily, well,

00:39:58.410 --> 00:40:00.640
it would plunge like 90%.

00:40:00.640 --> 00:40:02.640
So it's very much in the
company's best interest

00:40:02.640 --> 00:40:04.560
to have our team members
be healthy as possible.

00:40:04.560 --> 00:40:06.351
Now, obviously, it's
in their best interest

00:40:06.351 --> 00:40:08.300
to be as healthy as possible.

00:40:08.300 --> 00:40:10.080
So what we do is--

00:40:10.080 --> 00:40:12.540
I've heard criticism of
our discount program,

00:40:12.540 --> 00:40:16.740
because it says like you're
favoring the healthy people

00:40:16.740 --> 00:40:19.980
and you're punishing the
people who need it the most,

00:40:19.980 --> 00:40:24.464
kind of that Marxist argument
of need should triumph.

00:40:24.464 --> 00:40:27.130
So we have an another program we
call the Total Health Immersion

00:40:27.130 --> 00:40:27.750
Program.

00:40:27.750 --> 00:40:30.690
This one is the one that
inspired me to write the book,

00:40:30.690 --> 00:40:34.940
because we have now sent over
4,000 of our team members--

00:40:34.940 --> 00:40:37.350
this says 3,400, but
it's not updated.

00:40:37.350 --> 00:40:40.530
We've now sent over 4,000 team
members through this program

00:40:40.530 --> 00:40:43.050
since we launched it in 2009.

00:40:43.050 --> 00:40:44.400
It's a one-week program.

00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:47.100
Costs about $4,000 a team
member to send somebody

00:40:47.100 --> 00:40:48.910
through the program,
medically supervised.

00:40:48.910 --> 00:40:52.069
For one week, we completely
control their food.

00:40:52.069 --> 00:40:53.985
We do intensive education
about healthy eating

00:40:53.985 --> 00:40:55.200
and healthy lifestyle.

00:40:55.200 --> 00:40:57.660
We put them on an
exercise program.

00:40:57.660 --> 00:41:00.240
We take all their biometrics
when they walk in,

00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:02.040
get their blood.

00:41:02.040 --> 00:41:06.450
We meet with a medical doctor,
and a week later, we do it

00:41:06.450 --> 00:41:07.880
all over on their way out.

00:41:07.880 --> 00:41:12.750
And even in one week, people
can make astounding progress.

00:41:12.750 --> 00:41:13.410
It's amazing.

00:41:13.410 --> 00:41:15.680
These are the average
results where cholesterol

00:41:15.680 --> 00:41:20.310
drops 24 points, triglycerides
24, BMI drops, blood pressure

00:41:20.310 --> 00:41:23.850
drops, and people lose
weight in just a week.

00:41:23.850 --> 00:41:25.545
Through this
program, our company

00:41:25.545 --> 00:41:28.710
has reversed type 2 diabetes
for hundreds of people.

00:41:28.710 --> 00:41:31.870
We have reversed heart
disease for many, many people.

00:41:31.870 --> 00:41:35.520
And I've seen hundreds of people
lose over 100 pounds of weight

00:41:35.520 --> 00:41:38.100
in less than a year or
a little over a year.

00:41:41.211 --> 00:41:42.086
Here's a typical guy.

00:41:42.086 --> 00:41:46.710
This is a store team leader
in the Sacramento area.

00:41:46.710 --> 00:41:48.180
He was type 2 diabetic.

00:41:48.180 --> 00:41:50.190
He reversed it very quickly.

00:41:50.190 --> 00:41:51.430
He lost over 90 pounds.

00:41:51.430 --> 00:41:55.424
