156 over 96 to 115 over 75.

00:41:55.424 --> 00:41:57.090
And he was diabetic,
and his blood sugar

00:41:57.090 --> 00:41:59.465
is between 70 and 80, which
is an excellent score, better

00:41:59.465 --> 00:42:01.950
than mine.

00:42:01.950 --> 00:42:03.027
Here's another guy.

00:42:03.027 --> 00:42:04.360
This guy lives in the Bay Area--

00:42:04.360 --> 00:42:06.060
no, he lives in Colorado.

00:42:06.060 --> 00:42:10.830
And this guy, he's now lost
over 100 pounds in the last 12

00:42:10.830 --> 00:42:11.580
months.

00:42:11.580 --> 00:42:13.380
He's now dropped
all his medications.

00:42:13.380 --> 00:42:16.290
He actually wrote a book called
"The Change," because he was so

00:42:16.290 --> 00:42:17.284
pumped up about this.

00:42:17.284 --> 00:42:18.700
And I think he's
left the company.

00:42:18.700 --> 00:42:22.230
I think he's now like a
permanent kind of a "Biggest

00:42:22.230 --> 00:42:23.820
Loser" promoter.

00:42:27.180 --> 00:42:29.520
So let me conclude, and
then I'll take questions.

00:42:29.520 --> 00:42:33.017
So our country is
overweight and unhealthy.

00:42:33.017 --> 00:42:35.100
And here's the thing--
it's completely reversible.

00:42:35.100 --> 00:42:39.360
We can reverse it through
diet and lifestyle.

00:42:39.360 --> 00:42:42.090
We should-- each of
has the potential

00:42:42.090 --> 00:42:43.442
to probably live to be 100.

00:42:43.442 --> 00:42:45.150
Now, I know Google is
going to figure out

00:42:45.150 --> 00:42:47.280
some technological
innovations that

00:42:47.280 --> 00:42:50.000
will help us to live past 100.

00:42:50.000 --> 00:42:53.250
The joke I say is that by
the time I get to be 100,

00:42:53.250 --> 00:42:55.860
they're going to figure out
how to keep me alive forever

00:42:55.860 --> 00:42:59.100
at the age of 100.

00:42:59.100 --> 00:43:01.710
But truthfully, the degenerative
diseases that are killing

00:43:01.710 --> 00:43:05.660
everybody-- heart disease,
cancer, and diabetes--

00:43:05.660 --> 00:43:08.310
are primarily dietary
and lifestyle diseases.

00:43:08.310 --> 00:43:09.990
80% of what we
spend on health care

00:43:09.990 --> 00:43:14.280
goes to treat these diseases
that we shouldn't even get.

00:43:14.280 --> 00:43:17.160
So my final message
is that each of us

00:43:17.160 --> 00:43:20.820
is being called to embark on a
hero's journey here in health.

00:43:20.820 --> 00:43:23.652
First, you have to wake up,
you have to become conscious,

00:43:23.652 --> 00:43:25.110
you have to change
the way you eat,

00:43:25.110 --> 00:43:27.150
and you have to
change your lifestyle.

00:43:27.150 --> 00:43:29.815
And then you're in a position
to go help other people.

00:43:29.815 --> 00:43:31.440
I actually wrote this
book because I've

00:43:31.440 --> 00:43:33.420
seen my own health transformed.

00:43:33.420 --> 00:43:35.940
I've seen hundreds and
perhaps to this point

00:43:35.940 --> 00:43:39.450
thousands of people in my own
company transform their health.

00:43:39.450 --> 00:43:41.700
And I felt an
ethical compunction

00:43:41.700 --> 00:43:44.190
to try to share what I've
learned, hence why I'm with you

00:43:44.190 --> 00:43:45.130
today.

00:43:45.130 --> 00:43:47.190
And thank you very much.

