my question is I see that

00:50:57.120 --> 00:50:59.850
in the book, but I don't really
see that in Whole Foods stores.

00:50:59.850 --> 00:51:04.230
And I understand that if you're
having third-party suppliers,

00:51:04.230 --> 00:51:06.652
for example, processed
foods and all

00:51:06.652 --> 00:51:08.550
of that might be really
hard to actually get

00:51:08.550 --> 00:51:12.060
90% of your food in the
store should be plant based.

00:51:12.060 --> 00:51:13.474
But then when you
have foods that

00:51:13.474 --> 00:51:15.390
are, for example, the
pastries at Whole Foods,

00:51:15.390 --> 00:51:17.910
the different foods
that are catered there,

00:51:17.910 --> 00:51:21.420
do you have a plan to move to
90% of it being plant based,

00:51:21.420 --> 00:51:22.680
not only for the health--

00:51:22.680 --> 00:51:24.900
JOHN MACKEY: Yeah, I
wrote a book about it.

00:51:24.900 --> 00:51:27.450
Let me ask you a question.

00:51:27.450 --> 00:51:28.590
I know your question.

00:51:28.590 --> 00:51:33.930
So the very first store I
opened before Whole Foods Market

00:51:33.930 --> 00:51:35.460
was called Safer Way.

00:51:35.460 --> 00:51:37.620
I opened that--

00:51:37.620 --> 00:51:39.990
I opened that in 1978.

00:51:39.990 --> 00:51:41.880
And it was a vegetarian store.

00:51:41.880 --> 00:51:43.445
It sold no meat.

00:51:43.445 --> 00:51:44.700
It sold no sugar.

00:51:44.700 --> 00:51:47.160
It sold no white flour.

00:51:47.160 --> 00:51:48.800
It sold no at alcohol.

00:51:48.800 --> 00:51:50.610
It sold no coffee.

00:51:50.610 --> 00:51:52.920
It was an incredibly
healthy store.

00:51:52.920 --> 00:51:55.920
And it did almost no business.

00:51:55.920 --> 00:51:58.920
It wasn't until we
relocated that store

00:51:58.920 --> 00:52:01.350
and began to sell the
foods that people wanted

00:52:01.350 --> 00:52:03.720
to buy that we had a business.

00:52:03.720 --> 00:52:06.830
And it was still a
natural food, primarily

00:52:06.830 --> 00:52:09.690
organic-oriented store.

00:52:09.690 --> 00:52:13.020
But we did sell meat,
natural meat, organic meat.

00:52:13.020 --> 00:52:16.374
We did begin to sell
beer and wine and coffee.

00:52:16.374 --> 00:52:18.165
And we sold some things
with sugar in them.

00:52:18.165 --> 00:52:19.740
We sold some white flour.

00:52:19.740 --> 00:52:21.750
And the store was
a huge success.

00:52:21.750 --> 00:52:23.730
So the ultimate answer
is, Whole Foods,

00:52:23.730 --> 00:52:25.650
like every other
business person,

00:52:25.650 --> 00:52:28.224
has to meet the market
where it finds it.

00:52:28.224 --> 00:52:29.640
And we have the
highest standards.

00:52:29.640 --> 00:52:31.520
I challenge you to
find any other chain

00:52:31.520 --> 00:52:34.380
of stores that has higher
nutritional standards

00:52:34.380 --> 00:52:35.550
as Whole Foods has.

00:52:35.550 --> 00:52:36.760
Nobody does.

00:52:36.760 --> 00:52:41.250
Yet it's not the ideal scenario
in terms of people's health,

00:52:41.250 --> 00:52:44.250
because people keep
making bad choices.

00:52:44.250 --> 00:52:46.700
And we have to serve
the customers that

00:52:46.700 --> 00:52:49.320
are going to go down the street
to get what they want to get.

00:52:49.320 --> 00:52:53.670
So I hear what you're
saying, but I'm not

00:52:53.670 --> 00:52:56.460
sure what to do about it,
except try to convince people

00:52:56.460 --> 00:52:59.230
to vote those products
out of existence.

00:52:59.230 --> 00:53:02.160
I spoke last night in Palo
Alto at the Commonwealth Club,

00:53:02.160 --> 00:53:04.350
and I had animal
rights activists

00:53:04.350 --> 00:53:07.110
that were disrupting the event.

00:53:07.110 --> 00:53:09.680
You know, accusing me of
killing all these animals,

00:53:09.680 --> 00:53:12.450
and it's like guys, I don't
want to kill any animals.

00:53:12.450 --> 00:53:13.300
I don't eat them.

00:53:13.300 --> 00:53:15.620
I encourage you not to eat them.

00:53:15.620 --> 00:53:17.650
But we're in business.

00:53:17.650 --> 00:53:20.740
We have to serve the
market as we find it.

00:53:20.740 --> 00:53:23.380
And that's true for all
the foods that we sell.

00:53:23.380 --> 00:53:25.600
All I can try to do is
educate and persuade.

00:53:25.600 --> 00:53:27.730
Ultimately, you
make the choices.

00:53:27.730 --> 00:53:30.100
And if you don't
choose the meat,

00:53:30.100 --> 00:53:33.740
and you don't choose the
sugar and refined products,

00:53:33.740 --> 00:53:35.460
then we'll stop selling them.

