00:56:22.890 --> 00:56:25.970
and it's been somewhat of a
process kind of cutting out

00:56:25.970 --> 00:56:27.382
red meat, becoming vegetarian.

00:56:27.382 --> 00:56:28.340
JOHN MACKEY: A journey.

00:56:28.340 --> 00:56:28.839
I get it.

00:56:28.839 --> 00:56:30.860
AUDIENCE: Yeah, and as
the education builds,

00:56:30.860 --> 00:56:32.460
you start to make
better choices.

00:56:32.460 --> 00:56:36.410
So I'm just kind of curious
how that path for you was.

00:56:36.410 --> 00:56:37.940
Was it gradual?

00:56:37.940 --> 00:56:39.030
Was there a wow moment?

00:56:39.030 --> 00:56:40.910
JOHN MACKEY: Yeah,
several wow moments.

00:56:40.910 --> 00:56:42.990
In my case, it followed
through certain stages.

00:56:42.990 --> 00:56:45.470
The first one was when
I was 23 years old,

00:56:45.470 --> 00:56:49.420
and I moved into a vegetarian
co-op in Austin where I live.

00:56:49.420 --> 00:56:51.470
I wasn't vegetarian,
but I just thought

00:56:51.470 --> 00:56:54.500
I'd meet some really cool
people that were vegetarians.

00:56:54.500 --> 00:56:57.800
And that was a very
radical thing back in 1975

00:56:57.800 --> 00:56:59.330
to be a vegetarian.

00:56:59.330 --> 00:57:00.860
And I went in.

00:57:00.860 --> 00:57:03.140
I became a vegetarian,
and my food consciousness

00:57:03.140 --> 00:57:04.370
was awakened.

00:57:04.370 --> 00:57:06.600
When I went there,
it changed my life.

00:57:06.600 --> 00:57:09.807
I found my higher
purpose in life,

00:57:09.807 --> 00:57:11.390
although I didn't
know it at the time.

00:57:11.390 --> 00:57:14.000
I became a food
buyer for the co-op.

00:57:14.000 --> 00:57:15.490
I just read so many
books about it.

00:57:15.490 --> 00:57:17.198
I was totally in love
with the whole idea

00:57:17.198 --> 00:57:18.790
of natural and organic.

00:57:18.790 --> 00:57:22.190
And pretty soon after
that, I started Safer Way

00:57:22.190 --> 00:57:26.630
and with my girlfriend
that I met at that co-op.

00:57:26.630 --> 00:57:29.960
So that was the first awakening.

00:57:29.960 --> 00:57:33.384
And then the second
awakening was back in 2003

00:57:33.384 --> 00:57:35.842
when Whole Foods was being--
we were at the annual meeting,

00:57:35.842 --> 00:57:40.371
and we were disrupted
by animal activists who

00:57:40.371 --> 00:57:42.620
were very upset about a duck
we were selling that they

00:57:42.620 --> 00:57:44.480
said was from a factory farm.

00:57:44.480 --> 00:57:47.810
And to make a long story
short, I ended up in a dialogue

00:57:47.810 --> 00:57:51.200
with one of the activists,
and we swapped emails,

00:57:51.200 --> 00:57:52.850
and we began a dialogue.

00:57:52.850 --> 00:57:55.025
And after about
a month or so, we

00:57:55.025 --> 00:57:56.900
were both getting
frustrated with each other.

00:57:56.900 --> 00:57:58.520
And she sent me an
email and she said,

00:57:58.520 --> 00:58:00.980
you know, Mr. Mackey,
I can see that you're

00:58:00.980 --> 00:58:02.500
a very idealistic man.

00:58:02.500 --> 00:58:05.150
You really want to make
the world a better place.

00:58:05.150 --> 00:58:06.890
But when it comes to
livestock animals,

00:58:06.890 --> 00:58:08.681
you have no idea what
you're talking about.

00:58:08.681 --> 00:58:11.480
You're grossly
not well-informed.

00:58:11.480 --> 00:58:12.570
So I took that.

00:58:12.570 --> 00:58:15.290
I was taken aback, but I decided
you know, she's probably right.

00:58:15.290 --> 00:58:17.510
So then I read,
that summer of 2003,

00:58:17.510 --> 00:58:23.177
I read a dozen books on the
way we raise food in America,

00:58:23.177 --> 00:58:24.260
particularly animal foods.

00:58:24.260 --> 00:58:25.384
And I was like freaked out.

00:58:25.384 --> 00:58:26.227
It was terrible.

00:58:26.227 --> 00:58:26.810
I had no idea.

00:58:26.810 --> 00:58:27.770
It was so horrible.

00:58:27.770 --> 00:58:29.060
It's a nightmare.

00:58:29.060 --> 00:58:32.004
And by the time that I had
read about four or five books,

00:58:32.004 --> 00:58:33.920
I decided I'm going to
have to become a vegan.

00:58:33.920 --> 00:58:36.080
I can't in good
conscience eat this stuff.

00:58:36.080 --> 00:58:36.720
And so I did.

00:58:36.720 --> 00:58:38.370
That was a huge
awakening for me,

00:58:38.370 --> 00:58:40.200
and I also vowed at
that point Whole Foods

00:58:40.200 --> 00:58:43.140
would do what it could to
improve animal welfare.

00:58:43.140 --> 00:58:46.160
And that resulted in our
five-step animal welfare

00:58:46.160 --> 00:58:52.330
process that he has friends
that are unhappy with it.

00:58:52.330 --> 00:58:54.530
And then my health got better.

00:58:54.530 --> 00:58:56.360
But then the next
big breakthrough

00:58:56.360 --> 00:59:00.230
was like in 2006 when I
read "The China Study"

00:59:00.230 --> 00:59:01.610
by Colin Campbell.

00:59:01.610 --> 00:59:05.000
And that was like such an
awakening, because I really

00:59:05.000 --> 00:59:09.950
didn't stop eating
the processed foods.

00:59:09.950 --> 00:59:12.470
Even when I became a vegan,
I was like a junk food vegan.

00:59:12.470 --> 00:59:14.840
So when I got rid of
the processed foods,

00:59:14.840 --> 00:59:17.730
my health became unbelievable.

00:59:17.730 --> 00:59:19.670
I weigh the same
right now as I weighed

00:59:19.670 --> 00:59:21.290
when I was 18 years old.

00:59:21.290 --> 00:59:23.690
My cholesterol is like 135, 140.

00:59:23.690 --> 00:59:27.895
My blood pressure is 105
over 65, something like that.

00:59:27.895 --> 00:59:28.895
I almost never get sick.

00:59:28.895 --> 00:59:30.320
My immune system
is super strong.

00:59:30.320 --> 00:59:32.990
My telomeres are like
in the 98th percentile.

00:59:32.990 --> 00:59:34.890
Really, it's diet and lifestyle.

00:59:34.890 --> 00:59:38.030
And so those three
separate events,

00:59:38.030 --> 00:59:40.340
wish I had gotten when
I was in my early 20s.

00:59:40.340 --> 00:59:41.350
But I didn't.

00:59:41.350 --> 00:59:42.860
I only got part of
it when I was 23.

00:59:42.860 --> 00:59:45.350
I had to pick up the
rest as I got older.

00:59:45.350 --> 00:59:47.245
So good luck to you.

