You're going to get enough fat.

01:00:24.760 --> 01:00:27.680
But you are using oil
to cook, and we do

01:00:27.680 --> 01:00:29.000
argue against oil in the book.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:30.980
You don't need any-- you
never need to eat oil.

01:00:30.980 --> 01:00:33.260
You don't need to cook with it.

01:00:33.260 --> 01:00:36.050
I steam fry my veggies.

01:00:36.050 --> 01:00:38.020
And it's easy to do.

01:00:38.020 --> 01:00:39.920
You just do it with
water or vegetable

01:00:39.920 --> 01:00:42.740
broth or even a
little wine, which

01:00:42.740 --> 01:00:44.630
alcohol will evaporate off.

01:00:44.630 --> 01:00:47.930
So you don't need that to saute.

01:00:47.930 --> 01:00:51.110
And if you're talking about
fats to add some kind of sauce

01:00:51.110 --> 01:00:53.310
to say put on the
veggies and stuff,

01:00:53.310 --> 01:00:56.570
it's so easy if you get a
high-powered blender like

01:00:56.570 --> 01:00:59.930
a Vitamix or a Blendtec or
even a little NutriBullet,

01:00:59.930 --> 01:01:01.780
you can make--

01:01:01.780 --> 01:01:03.870
you just mix nuts and seeds.

01:01:03.870 --> 01:01:07.420
I mean, a simple way to do it
is some kind of nut or seed,

01:01:07.420 --> 01:01:09.680
a little bit of some kind
of vinegar or lemon juice,

01:01:09.680 --> 01:01:12.020
and fat and acid.

01:01:12.020 --> 01:01:15.849
And then either you go savory
with like garlic and mustard

01:01:15.849 --> 01:01:18.140
or something like that or
you go sweet by just throwing

01:01:18.140 --> 01:01:21.050
like blueberries or blackberries
into it or cherries,

01:01:21.050 --> 01:01:23.240
and you'll get the
most delicious sauces

01:01:23.240 --> 01:01:24.950
you can possibly imagine.

01:01:24.950 --> 01:01:27.590
And so a typical dinner
for me, for example,

01:01:27.590 --> 01:01:33.260
is I cook a sweet potato, steam
up a big plate of veggies,

01:01:33.260 --> 01:01:36.240
make up some kind of
little nut dressing

01:01:36.240 --> 01:01:39.040
and put that on the
veggies and voila.

01:01:39.040 --> 01:01:41.490
Takes me 10 minutes
to cook dinner

01:01:41.490 --> 01:01:43.200
or after you get
the sweet potato,

01:01:43.200 --> 01:01:45.517
you've got to bake
that or steam it.

01:01:45.517 --> 01:01:46.850
But that takes very little time.

01:01:46.850 --> 01:01:48.070
It's not expensive at all.

01:01:48.070 --> 01:01:50.760
It's delicious, and it's
incredibly nutritious,

01:01:50.760 --> 01:01:52.040
and couldn't be easier.

01:01:52.040 --> 01:01:57.380
So I get my fats from the Whole
Foods avocados, nuts and seeds,

01:01:57.380 --> 01:01:59.180
primarily the
concentrated sources.

01:01:59.180 --> 01:02:01.040
But what people don't
realize, fats are--

01:02:01.040 --> 01:02:01.985
they're in everything.

01:02:01.985 --> 01:02:04.310
You can't possibly
not get enough fat.

01:02:04.310 --> 01:02:06.350
If I had steel cut
oats for breakfast,

01:02:06.350 --> 01:02:13.100
and oats are 13% fat,
just regular oats, fats,

01:02:13.100 --> 01:02:14.586
they're just there.

01:02:14.586 --> 01:02:17.346
It's like not something
to worry about.

